An Act authorizing the city of Salem to prohibit the application of second generation anti-
coagulant rodenticides within its borders.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding chapter 132B of the general laws or any other general or
2 special law to the contrary, the city of Salem may by ordinance prohibit the application of second
3 generation anti-coagulant rodenticides within the City of Salem, including application of such
4 pesticides by licensed commercial applicators as defined in 333 C.M.R 10.00.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
